class="comment__09f24__D0cxf y-css-1wfz87z"><span class=" raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">I love this location the most because of the simple fact that it never sounds like a night club when you walk in. I work from my phone/laptop and need to be able to hear my own thoughts. Other locations in this area need to take a hint from this Starbucks. Nice, peaceful environment where I can actually concentrate or have a conversation. Not to mention, they get the drinks right every single time. I'd love it better if they had compost straws and packaging. But this Starbucks has a nice, comfy seating area for friends, there's a business area to work, and high and low top tables. The staff are just the reason I keep coming back. data-font-weight="semibold"><a href="/biz_photos/starbucks-broomfield-17?userid=zmNtZJGeyuMRcvLBmY0_SA" class="y-css-1x1e1r2">7 photos</a></span></div></div><div class=" y-css-1pnalxe"><p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf y-css-1wfz87z"><span class=" raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">New store built to current Starbucks corporate standards. Not squeezed in at an existing location and renovated. This is the Starbucks image currently with nitro cold brew and regular cold brew on tap. Drive through. Mobile ordering. Single seating, chairs for longing surrounded by beautiful succulents, large tables where groups can work, or you can spread out to achieve project success! <br><br>Seems Starbucks is building in new developments. Good plan as they can become a neighborhood go to, build the store to their specifications, the Walmart of coffee. I know a lot of people don't like Starbucks. I never said it was the best coffee or snacks. Just a generally quiet spot to use free Wifi or get some work done.<br><br>Could be a nice spot to hang out if parents drop kids off early for a 1st Bank Center concert. Or even to get a pick me up if nearby Seven Eleven coffee doesn't work for you. I did see a smaller coffee shop nearer to all the condos and apartments nearby.<br><br>I didn't have any issues with Wifi when I visited. Several previous reviews mention that so beware I guess. I think the food supply issues were due to the store being new. Everyone I saw in the store had food and drink in hand and chatted or typed on their laptops merrily.</span></p></div><div class=" y-css-2w187z"><div class="y-css-1orb10f"><div 2024</span></div></div></div><div class=" y-css-1pnalxe"><p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf y-css-1wfz87z"><span class=" raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">Horrible horrible customer service at this relatively new Starbucks location off Wadsworth near the hospital near WeatherTech. Been there a few times and each time totally new employees. So a lot of turnover. However the logistics of their ordering/serving process make no sense. So I go inside and order coffee and a muffin or other pastry The person at the register gives me my coffee. So far so good. From there it goes downhill and the muffin order (this has happened numerous times) is routed to a person in the back at the vehicle line window and the muffin order (whether heated or not) is lost. When it finally does come out which is usually a good 10 minutes later (even unheated) it is placed in a bag on a tray behind the counter. From there numerous coffee makers walk by it for another good 10 minutes until I finally say "that's my muffin that been sitting there for the last 10 minutes while you walked by and ignored it. " Someone then usually says "that's not my job the vehicle line person is supposed to give you a muffin." So totally f'd up. Alao you can never never figure out who the manager is at at Starbucks to complain to and possible get their logistical problems fixed.</span></p></div><div class="arrange__09f24__LDfbs                         if (!f._fbq) f._fbq = n;
                        n.push = n;
                        n.loaded = !0;
                        n.version = '2.0';
                        n.queue = [];
                        t = b.createElement(e);
                        t.async = !0;
                        t.src = v;
                        s = b.getElementsByTagName(e)[0];
                        s.parentNode.insertBefore(t, s);
                    })(window, document, 'script', 'https://connect.facebook.net/en_US/fbevents.js');

                    fbq('dataProcessingOptions', ['LDU']);
